Sentencas: BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta as a candidate electrolyte material is prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine-nitrate process.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: After calcining at 900 degrees C, the single-phase perovskite is obtained due to the better distribution of starting materials and the more feasible reaction kinetic conditions than solid state reaction method.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: The relative densities reach 96.8 and 98.4% respectively after sintering the pressed pellets at 1280 and 1400 degrees C for 10 h. In humidified oxygen the ionic conductivities are 0.015, 0.045, 0.101 and 0.207 S cm(-1) at 500, 600, 700 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: In air and humidified oxygen the activation energies for ionic conductivity are 66.1 and 68.9 kJ mol(-1).
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: In humidified hydrogen, however, different activation energies occur in low and high temperature ranges.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: The thermal expansion curve inflections at 500-800 degrees C with respect to possible phase changes are found.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: Zirconia aggregation possibly results in the higher activation energy and peculiar thermal expansion behavior.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity, sintering and thermal expansion behaviors of mixed ion conductor BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ prepared by ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine nitrate process

Sentencas: The results indicate the ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid assisted glycine-nitrate process is a very promising preparation method for solid oxide fuel cell practical application.
